\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces  RPS game with $c=-0.8$, $w=0.3$. The blue line corresponds to a numerical solution of the adjusted replicator dynamics for the Moran process, and the green line is a Moran process agent based simulation with $N = 500$. Negative real part of eigenvalues (see appendix) produces a spiral sink for the replicator systems, and trajectories spiral inwards to the fixed point $\left (\frac  {1}{3},\frac  {1}{3},\frac  {1}{3}\right )$. At $N=500$, simulation tracks the deterministic trajectory with small deviations due to finite population size noise.}}{2}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:rps_sink}{{2}{2}{RPS game with $c=-0.8$, $w=0.3$. The blue line corresponds to a numerical solution of the adjusted replicator dynamics for the Moran process, and the green line is a Moran process agent based simulation with $N = 500$. Negative real part of eigenvalues (see appendix) produces a spiral sink for the replicator systems, and trajectories spiral inwards to the fixed point $\left (\frac {1}{3},\frac {1}{3},\frac {1}{3}\right )$. At $N=500$, simulation tracks the deterministic trajectory with small deviations due to finite population size noise}{figure.2}{}}
